# Portfolio V3 — Mobile Support

All rules in this file apply to `src/v3/**` only. Cross-read [`v3-components.mdc`](v3-components.mdc) for component-level conventions and [`v3-design-system.mdc`](v3-design-system.mdc) for palette/type tokens.

---

## Touch navigation

- Attach the `useSwipeHandler` hook ([`src/v3/components/SwipeHandler.js`](src/v3/components/SwipeHandler.js)) to the `.sections-container` / `v3-portfolio-root` wrapper — **not** to individual sections.
- Minimum swipe delta: **50 px** vertical before triggering a section change.
- Use `{ passive: true }` on `touchstart` and `touchend` listeners to keep scroll performance smooth.
- Prevent double-firing: guard with a `useRef` boolean lock that resets after the slide transition finishes (same pattern as `isTransitioningRef`).

---

## Tap targets

- **Minimum 44 × 44 px** for every interactive control: nav dots, hamburger icon, close button, expand/collapse toggles, filter buttons, form submit.
- Extend the hit area with a transparent `::after` pseudo-element (`inset: -8px`) rather than inflating the visible element.
- On mobile, nav dots get `width: 8px; height: 8px` visually but the `::after` inset makes them 24 × 24 px effective.

---

## Navigation layout on mobile (≤ 768 px)

- **Nav dots**: move from the fixed right vertical column to a **fixed horizontal bottom tray** (`bottom: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0px))`; `flex-direction: row`).
- **Hamburger menu** ([`src/v3/components/HamburgerMenu.js`](src/v3/components/HamburgerMenu.js)): shown only on mobile; replaces the desktop right-rail with a full-screen green overlay (`$green-dark` bg, `v3-nav-overlay`).
- **Arrow buttons** (up/down): visible on mobile above the bottom dot tray (`bottom: calc(72px + safe-area-inset-bottom))`; 44×44 px tap targets. Swipe and hamburger remain available.
- **Chat FAB** ([`src/components/ChatAgent.js`](src/components/ChatAgent.js)): bottom-left on mobile (icon only); nav dots stay bottom-center — avoid overlap.
- **Desktop nav links** in the header bar: hidden on mobile (`v3-header` hides the `<nav>` via `isMobile` from the zustand store).

---

## Safe areas (notch / home indicator)

Apply `env(safe-area-inset-*)` to every fixed-position element:

```scss
// Header
padding-top: calc(#{$space-3} + env(safe-area-inset-top, 0px));

// Bottom dots tray
bottom: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0px));

// Hamburger button
top:   calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-top, 0px));
right: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-right, 0px));

// Nav overlay (full-screen)
padding: env(safe-area-inset-top, 0)
         env(safe-area-inset-right, 0)
         env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0)
         env(safe-area-inset-left, 0);
```

The `<meta name="viewport">` tag in `public/index.html` must include `viewport-fit=cover` for safe-area insets to work:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover" />
```

---

## Section height

- Use `100vh` with a `100svh` override for the small viewport height (excludes the mobile browser chrome bar):
  ```scss
  height: 100vh;   /* fallback for browsers without svh support */
  height: 100svh;  /* override — excludes mobile browser chrome */
  ```
- Apply on `.v3-section-slide` (individual section wrappers) and `.v3-portfolio-root`.
- Each `.v3-section-slide` is `position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%` and slides in/out via `transform: translateY(${offset * 100}vh)`.
- Add `padding-top: calc(60px + env(safe-area-inset-top, 0px))` on `.v3-section-slide` to push section content below the fixed header.
- Never use `100%` on section root elements — it resolves relative to the parent which may differ from the viewport.

---

## Font sizes

- **Minimum 16 px on all `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<select>` elements** to prevent iOS Safari auto-zoom on focus. The `.v3-form__control` class sets `font-size: 16px`.
- Hero headings: use `clamp()` — e.g. `clamp(2.2rem, 7vw, 5rem)` — so they scale gracefully from 320 px up to 1280 px+.
- Section titles: `clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.8rem)`.
- Body copy minimum: **0.875 rem** (14 px) on small phones; prefer `0.9 rem` — `1 rem` for comfortable reading.

---

## Image sizing

- Every `<img>` inside sections must have:
  ```css
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  ```
- Profile image and project thumbnails: `object-fit: cover` to fill their containers without distortion.
- Use `loading="lazy"` on project thumbnails and any non-hero images.
- Decorative/background images: `role="presentation"` and `alt=""`.

---

## Overflow

- Every `.v3-section-slide` wrapper: `overflow: hidden` — prevents inner content from breaking the slide boundary on small screens.
- Scrollable section content (Experience list, Projects grid): use a nested `.v3-scrollable` wrapper (`overflow-y: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; overscroll-behavior: contain`), **not** the section root.
- `html, body { overflow: hidden }` is set globally in `v3-app.scss` — do not override this on the section root elements.
- `.v3-portfolio-root` is `position: fixed; inset: 0; overflow: hidden` — it is the stacking container for all `position: fixed` section slides.

---

## Performance

- Lazy-load project thumbnails: `<img loading="lazy" />`.
- Defer image `src` assignment: set `data-src` and swap `src` in the `onLoad` handler (or use a lightweight Intersection Observer only for the lazy loader, not for animation triggers).
- Reduce motion: `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` disables all transitions and spring animations (already in `v3-app.scss`).
- Keep each section's own JS light: heavy data arrays (`EXPERIENCES`, `COMPANIES`) are module-level constants — they parse once per bundle, not per render.
